    "created_at": "2016-11-19T11:48:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-19T11:49:30Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "By the way, my intention is to move the `AmmoPool`-reloading logic to a separate, upgradable `ReloadAmmo` trait, because that would allow modders to modify reloading without touching the AmmoPool(s) directly. \nThis can then be used to speed up or enable/disable reloading via upgrades, the latter allowing us to ditch the `Rearm` activity, too.\nSwitching between AmmoPools as they are now directly isn't as feasible, obviously, as that resets the current ammo state of weapons linked to the pool.\n\nEdit: It also means we can scrap some extra booleans like `SelfReloads`.\n"
  },
